<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,908,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[448,562,908,932]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[448,562,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poorly known in the Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1101,908,933]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Mexico</collectingCountry>
with only two species of this genus recorded from the region: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[514,621,944,968]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[514,621,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B. goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gravier 1908)" authorityName="Gravier" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Gravier" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[675,940,943,968]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="riveti">
<emphasis box="[675,764,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B. riveti</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gravier, M. C." box="[778,932,943,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="40 - 44" refId="ref13655" refString="Gravier, M. C. (1908) Sur les annelides polychetes rapportes par M. Le Dr. Rivet de Payta (Perou). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 14, 40 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 5649" type="journal article" year="1908">Gravier 1908</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Specially, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[1067,1173,944,968]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[1067,1173,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B. goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently is reported as having a wide distribution which includes Asia, Africa and both American coasts (
<bibRefCitation author="Webster, H. E." box="[1093,1254,980,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="305 - 327" refId="ref15636" refString="Webster, H. E. (1884) Annelida from Bermuda, collected by G. Brown Goode. Bulletin United States National Museum, 25, 305 - 327. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.25.305" type="journal article" year="1884">Webster 1884</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Augener, H." box="[1267,1431,980,1004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="67 - 625" refId="ref13025" refString="Augener, H. (1918) Polychaeta. Beitrage zur Kenntnis des Meeresfauna West-Afrikas. Fol. 2. Lief. 2. Herausgegeben von W. Michaelsen, Hamburg, 559 pp. [pp. 67 - 625]" type="book chapter" year="1918">Augener 1918</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monro, C. C. A." box="[151,298,1016,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref14583" refString="Monro, C. C. A. (1933) The Polychaeta Errantia collected by Dr C. Crossland at Colon, in the Panama Region, and the Galapagos Islands during the expedition of the S. Y. St. George. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1933, 1 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1933. tb 01578. x" type="journal article" year="1933">Monro 1933</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima, M. &amp; Hartman, O." box="[315,624,1015,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 237" refId="ref14100" refString="Imajima, M. &amp; Hartman, O. (1964) The polychaetous annelids of Japan. Part I. Allan Hancock Fundation Publications, Occasional paper, 26, 1 - 237." type="journal article" year="1964">Imajima &amp; Hartman 1964</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[648,850,1016,1040]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[648,850,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Bhawania goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Webster, H. E." box="[1077,1254,1015,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="305 - 327" refId="ref15636" refString="Webster, H. E. (1884) Annelida from Bermuda, collected by G. Brown Goode. Bulletin United States National Museum, 25, 305 - 327. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.25.305" type="journal article" year="1884">Webster (1884)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1436,1015,1040]" name="Bermuda" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
Island; later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T. H." box="[306,476,1052,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref14825" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins (1985)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species with specimens from Florida. This species has also been recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kudenov, J. D." box="[300,786,1087,1112]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="65 - 91" refId="ref14238" refString="Kudenov, J. D. (1975) Errant polychaetes from the Gulf of California. Journal of Natural History, 9, 65 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937500770061" type="journal article" year="1975">Kudenov (1975, Puerto Peñasco, Sonora)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauchald, K." box="[801,1279,1087,1112]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref13517" refString="Fauchald, K. (1977) Polychaetes from intertidal areas in Panama, with a review of previous shallow-water records. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 221, 1 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.221" type="journal article" year="1977">
Fauchald (1977, Taboga Island, 
<collectingCountry box="[1181,1272,1088,1112]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Panama</collectingCountry>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and Bastida- 
<bibRefCitation author="Bastida-Zavala, J. R." box="[151,639,1124,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="11 - 39" refId="ref13067" refString="Bastida-Zavala, J. R. (1993) Taxonomia y composicion biogeografica de los poliquetos (Annelida: Polychaeta) de la bahia de La Paz, B. C. S., Mexico. Revista de Investigacion Cientifica, UABCS, 4 (1), 11 - 39." type="journal article" year="1993">Zavala (1993, La Paz, Baja California Sur)</bibRefCitation>
. These records need to be thorougly checked as seems unlikely that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B. goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has traversed the 
<collectingCountry box="[432,521,1161,1184]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Panama</collectingCountry>
Canal to the Pacific coast of America. The specimen revised here agree with the redescription by 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T. H." box="[340,505,1196,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref14825" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins (1985)</bibRefCitation>
except for the presence of the nuchal fold (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T. H." box="[994,1256,1196,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref14825" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins 1985: fig. 21A</bibRefCitation>
). This character was not observed since the single specimen is damaged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation author="Gravier, M. C." box="[199,372,1268,1293]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="40 - 44" refId="ref13655" refString="Gravier, M. C. (1908) Sur les annelides polychetes rapportes par M. Le Dr. Rivet de Payta (Perou). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 14, 40 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 5649" type="journal article" year="1908">Gravier (1908)</bibRefCitation>
described briefly 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gravier" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[596,782,1268,1292]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="riveti">
<emphasis box="[596,782,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Bhawania riveti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on one incomplete specimen from Payta, 
<collectingCountry box="[1378,1433,1268,1292]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Perú</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[151,386,1303,1328]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[151,265,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Bhawania</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[310,386,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from Gravier’s in some features: notoaciculum in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gravier" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1044,1136,1304,1328]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="riveti">
<emphasis box="[1044,1136,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B. riveti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is wide and long (
<bibRefCitation author="Gravier, M. C." pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="93 - 126" refId="ref13709" refString="Gravier, M. C. (1910) Annelides polychetes recueillis a Payta (Perou) par M. le Dr. Rivet, Membre de la Mission geodesique de l'Equateur. In: France. Ministere de l'instruction publique, Mission du service geographique de l'Armee pour la mesure d'un arc de meridien equatorial en Amerique du Sud sous le controle scientifique de l'Academie des Sciences 1899 - 1906. Tome 9 (Zoologie). Fascicule 3 (Mollusques, Annelides, Oligochetes). Gauthier-Villars, Paris, pp. 93 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 980" type="book chapter" year="1910">Gravier 1910: pl. VII, fig.31</bibRefCitation>
) while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[460,601,1340,1365]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[460,484,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[525,601,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller and slimmer (
<figureCitation box="[876,966,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,200,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[170,1423,189,1942]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Bhawania cf. goodei. A, parapodium middle segment; B–E, neurochaetal types; F, lateral paleae; G, subunit 1 palea; H, meddle main palea; I–K, median paleae group. Scale bars: 30 µm (BCDE), 100 µm (FGHIJK), 200 µm (A)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2609674/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); regarding paleae fan, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravier, M. C." box="[1227,1394,1340,1365]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" pagination="40 - 44" refId="ref13655" refString="Gravier, M. C. (1908) Sur les annelides polychetes rapportes par M. Le Dr. Rivet de Payta (Perou). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 14, 40 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 5649" type="journal article" year="1908">Gravier (1908)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention if his species presented internal raised ribs in the paleae, character present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[1184,1331,1375,1400]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[1184,1208,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1255,1331,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; also the length of the paleae in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gravier" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[406,496,1413,1436]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="riveti">
<emphasis box="[406,496,1413,1436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B. riveti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is about 1/3 of body width, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1884" box="[910,1053,1412,1437]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="goodei">
<emphasis box="[910,927,1413,1436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">B</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis box="[977,1053,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">goodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is about 1/2 body width.
</paragraph>
